measure.CatchLine: Provides for an annual increase of three percent in the maximum assessed value of property.
measure.MeasureSummary:
Digest: The Act would increase the maximum value of property for each tax year by three percent. (Flesch Readability Score: 68.9). 
	Provides for an annual increase of three percent in the maximum assessed value of property. 
	Takes effect on the 91st day following adjournment sine die.
measure.RelatingToFull: Relating to maximum assessed value; creating new provisions; amending ORS 307.032, 308.146, 308.707, 308A.107, 308A.256, 308A.315, 321.354, 321.722, 321.833 and 358.505 and section 4, chapter 96, Oregon Laws 2016, and section 1, chapter 94, Oregon Laws 2024; and prescribing an effective date.
measure.RelatingTo: Relating to maximum assessed value; prescribing an effective date.
measure.FiscalImpact: May have fiscal impact, but no statement yet issued
measure.RevenueImpact: May have revenue impact, but no statement yet issued

historyActions.ActionText: Introduction and first reading. Referred to President's desk.
